1
00:00:14,211 --> 00:00:16,372
We're running low on résumés.

2
00:00:16,580 --> 00:00:19,344
You want a job
with Popular Mechanics?

3
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:23,577
If you're gonna work for mechanics,
those are the ones.

4
00:00:23,988 --> 00:00:28,652
Guys, I'm going for anything here.
I can't be a waitress anymore.

5
00:00:28,859 --> 00:00:33,990
I'm sick of the lousy tips.
I'm sick of being called "Excuse Me."

6
00:00:34,732 --> 00:00:38,395
-Paper cut! Paper cut!
-Here.

7
00:00:40,938 --> 00:00:43,736
Grapefruit juice! Grapefruit juice!

8
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:47,871
Okay, we're almost done.
Only 20 more to go.

9
00:00:48,078 --> 00:00:52,674
-Rach, did you proofread these?
-Yeah. Why?

10
00:00:53,183 --> 00:00:57,882
Nothing. I'm sure they'll be
impressed with your "compuper" skills.

11
00:00:58,255 --> 00:01:03,192
Oh, my God!
Do you think it's on all of them?

12
00:01:06,463 --> 00:01:10,126
No, I'm sure the Xerox machine
caught a few.

13
00:01:19,709 --> 00:01:21,836
The One With the Poker

14
00:02:09,326 --> 00:02:14,764
They call this a love seat but I'm not
feeling anything special towards you.

15
00:02:24,741 --> 00:02:26,504
-Hey, guys.
-Hey.

16
00:02:27,511 --> 00:02:29,103
Hi, ladies.

17
00:02:29,313 --> 00:02:32,771
Can I get you anything?
Did you bring the mail?

18
00:02:32,983 --> 00:02:37,283
-Lots of responses.
-Really? Sure, we have scones left!

19
00:02:37,888 --> 00:02:38,877
Read them.

20
00:02:39,089 --> 00:02:43,651
"Dear Miss Greene:
Thank you for your inquiry. However..."

21
00:02:44,495 --> 00:02:50,263
-We have apple cinnamon...
-"Dear Ms. Greene..." Yeah, yeah! No.

22
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:55,436
-What?
-Your Visa bill is huge!

23
00:02:56,773 --> 00:02:57,933
Give me that.

24
00:02:58,408 --> 00:03:01,571
Linda's great.
Why won't you go out with her?

25
00:03:01,778 --> 00:03:04,076
-I don't know.
-Is this about her...

26
00:03:04,281 --> 00:03:07,580
..."<i>The Flintstones</i> could
have really happened" thing?

27
00:03:07,784 --> 00:03:12,414
It's not just that. I want someone
who does something for me...

28
00:03:12,623 --> 00:03:14,614
...who gets my heart pounding.

29
00:03:15,726 --> 00:03:17,694
Who makes me...

30
00:03:19,329 --> 00:03:22,321
Little playthings with yarn?

31
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,765
What?

32
00:03:24,968 --> 00:03:27,801
Could you want her more?

33
00:03:28,238 --> 00:03:29,227
Who?

34
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:32,931
Dee, the sarcastic sister
from <i>What's Happening!!</i>

35
00:03:40,384 --> 00:03:43,148
Look, I'm totally over her.

36
00:03:43,353 --> 00:03:44,650
-Hi!
-Coffee?

37
00:03:44,855 --> 00:03:47,346
-No, we're fine.
-Okay.

38
00:03:52,763 --> 00:03:55,789
-Shut up!
-We're not saying anything.

39
00:03:55,999 --> 00:03:58,627
-What?
-Joey cried last night.

40
00:03:59,937 --> 00:04:03,304
-Thank you.
-We were playing poker...

41
00:04:03,507 --> 00:04:07,773
There was chocolate on the three.
It looked like an eight.

42
00:04:07,978 --> 00:04:11,436
You should have seen him.
"Read them and weep!"

43
00:04:11,648 --> 00:04:13,479
And then he did.

44
00:04:14,685 --> 00:04:18,485
Now, how come you guys
have never played poker with us?

45
00:04:18,689 --> 00:04:22,785
Yeah, what is that?
Like some kind of sexist guy thing?

46
00:04:22,993 --> 00:04:27,157
-It's poker, so only guys can play?
-No. Women can play.

47
00:04:27,364 --> 00:04:32,131
Then, what is it? Some kind of, like,
some kind of, you know...

48
00:04:32,336 --> 00:04:34,327
All right, what is it?

49
00:04:35,839 --> 00:04:37,966
There are just no women
in our game.

50
00:04:38,175 --> 00:04:41,975
We just don't know any
women who know how to play poker.

51
00:04:42,179 --> 00:04:45,615
That is a lame excuse.
It's a typical guy response.

52
00:04:45,816 --> 00:04:47,784
Do you know how to play?

53
00:04:48,352 --> 00:04:50,217
No.

54
00:04:51,321 --> 00:04:54,347
-But you could teach us.
-No.

55
00:04:59,129 --> 00:05:03,657
Okay, so now we draw cards.

56
00:05:06,303 --> 00:05:08,965
So I wouldn't need any.
I have a straight.

57
00:05:09,172 --> 00:05:12,107
-Oh, good for you!
-Congratulations!

58
00:05:14,544 --> 00:05:18,378
-Pheebs, how many do you want?
-I just need two.

59
00:05:18,582 --> 00:05:22,177
The 10 of spades and the 6 of clubs.

60
00:05:23,353 --> 00:05:26,686
-No, you can't...
-I have the 10 of spades! Here.

61
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:28,482
Thanks!

62
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:34,490
-No, you can't do that.
-Don't need them. I'm going for fours.

63
00:05:34,698 --> 00:05:36,393
Oh, you're...

64
00:05:37,668 --> 00:05:42,002
You're going for fours.
Chandler, could you...? Thanks, man.

65
00:05:47,010 --> 00:05:48,170
Here we go.

66
00:05:48,378 --> 00:05:51,472
We've got salmon roulettes
and crudités.

67
00:05:51,682 --> 00:05:53,513
What are you doing?

68
00:05:53,717 --> 00:05:57,551
In poker, there's no food
with more than one syllable.

69
00:05:57,754 --> 00:06:01,815
It's got to be like chips
or dip or pretz...

70
00:06:03,093 --> 00:06:08,258
I hope you'll let it slide just
this once. I was all out of "pretz."

71
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:10,995
Now the dealer...

72
00:06:11,201 --> 00:06:14,932
We got it. Let's play for real.
High stakes. Big bucks!

73
00:06:15,138 --> 00:06:20,166
You sure? Phoebe just threw away two
jacks because they didn't look happy.

74
00:06:23,847 --> 00:06:26,782
But I'm ready. So just deal.

75
00:06:26,983 --> 00:06:30,009
Okay, last-minute lesson!
Joey...

76
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,653
Three.

77
00:06:31,855 --> 00:06:32,844
Eight.

78
00:06:33,423 --> 00:06:36,620
Eight. Three.
All right, very good.

79
00:06:40,664 --> 00:06:42,529
Damn it, damn it, damn it!

80
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:46,260
Joey had two fives showing,
so for you to raise was...

81
00:06:46,470 --> 00:06:48,165
Yes?

82
00:06:48,372 --> 00:06:50,636
Downright gutsy.

83
00:06:52,976 --> 00:06:55,968
-I see, so you were lying.
-About what?

84
00:06:56,179 --> 00:06:59,342
-About how good your cards were.
-I was bluffing.

85
00:07:00,283 --> 00:07:02,581
And what is bluffing?

86
00:07:04,621 --> 00:07:07,818
Is it not another word for lying?

87
00:07:08,024 --> 00:07:13,223
Sorry to break up this party, but I've
got to go fax résumés before work.

88
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:15,898
-We've got to settle.
-Settle what?

89
00:07:17,501 --> 00:07:20,163
The Jamestown colony of Virginia.

90
00:07:21,838 --> 00:07:24,966
See, King George is giving us
the land...

91
00:07:27,711 --> 00:07:31,875
-The game, Rachel. You owe us money.
-Right.

92
00:07:32,082 --> 00:07:35,745
It's their first time.
Let's forget about the money.

93
00:07:35,952 --> 00:07:38,580
Hell, no. We'll pay!

94
00:07:38,789 --> 00:07:42,156
Monica, I had another
answer all ready.

95
00:07:43,493 --> 00:07:46,121
And you know what?
We want a rematch.

96
00:07:46,329 --> 00:07:49,890
That's fine with me.
Could use some money.

97
00:07:51,468 --> 00:07:56,462
-You're enjoying this, aren't you?
-Well, yeah, I am.

98
00:07:56,907 --> 00:08:01,105
So you get your ya-yas
by taking money from your friends.

99
00:08:02,712 --> 00:08:05,977
Yes, and I get my ya-yas from IKEA.

100
00:08:07,484 --> 00:08:11,545
You have to put them together
yourself, but they cost less.

101
00:08:12,222 --> 00:08:15,089
Look, this is poker.
I play to win.

102
00:08:15,292 --> 00:08:17,760
For me to win,
others have to lose.

103
00:08:17,961 --> 00:08:21,488
If you're gonna play,
don't expect me to be nice.

104
00:08:21,698 --> 00:08:24,633
Because once those cards are dealt...

105
00:08:33,810 --> 00:08:35,334
Yeah?

106
00:08:38,515 --> 00:08:41,177
I'm not a nice guy.

107
00:08:47,524 --> 00:08:49,185
All right, let's eat.

108
00:08:49,392 --> 00:08:53,226
Did you get that
from the "I Love Rachel Pizzeria"?

109
00:08:53,663 --> 00:08:57,497
-You still on that?
-What was with that Black Bart speech?

110
00:08:57,701 --> 00:09:01,068
"When I play poker,
I'm not a nice guy."

111
00:09:01,805 --> 00:09:03,238
You're way off.

112
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:07,069
No, I don't think so,
because I think you love her!

113
00:09:07,811 --> 00:09:12,510
No. I might have had feelings
for her at one time. Not anymore.

114
00:09:12,716 --> 00:09:13,774
I just...

115
00:09:13,984 --> 00:09:17,317
Marcel! Where are you going
with that disk?

116
00:09:17,521 --> 00:09:20,012
You are not putting that on again.

117
00:09:20,223 --> 00:09:24,182
If you press that button,
you are in very big trouble.

118
00:09:55,025 --> 00:09:57,653
You believe what a jerk
Ross was being?

119
00:09:57,861 --> 00:10:01,319
-Yeah, I know.
-He can get really competitive.

120
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,233
What?

121
00:10:05,669 --> 00:10:08,900
"Hello, kettle? This is Monica.
You're black!"

122
00:10:09,105 --> 00:10:10,936
Please!

123
00:10:13,643 --> 00:10:15,804
I'm not as bad as Ross.

124
00:10:16,012 --> 00:10:19,470
I beg to differ.
The Pictionary incident?

125
00:10:19,983 --> 00:10:21,780
That wasn't an incident.

126
00:10:21,985 --> 00:10:26,422
I was gesturing and the plate
slipped out of my hand.

127
00:10:30,327 --> 00:10:33,728
-I got an interview!
-You're kidding! Where?

128
00:10:33,930 --> 00:10:36,694
Saks Fifth Avenue.

129
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,595
Oh, Rachel!

130
00:10:39,069 --> 00:10:42,527
It's like the mother ship
is calling you home.

131
00:10:46,009 --> 00:10:50,002
-What's the job?
-Assistant buyer.

132
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:53,014
I would be shopping!

133
00:10:54,117 --> 00:10:56,585
For a living!

134
00:10:57,921 --> 00:11:01,880
That's Aunt Iris. She's been
playing poker since she was 5.

135
00:11:02,092 --> 00:11:05,061
You've got to listen
to every word she says.

136
00:11:05,562 --> 00:11:08,463
-Is Tony Randall dead?
-I don't think so.

137
00:11:08,665 --> 00:11:12,328
-He may be now. I hit him with my car.
-My God, really?

138
00:11:12,535 --> 00:11:15,993
No, that's bluffing.
Lesson number one.

139
00:11:17,374 --> 00:11:22,869
Let me tell you something. Everything
you hear at a poker game is pure crap!

140
00:11:23,079 --> 00:11:25,570
-Nice earrings.
-Thank you.

141
00:11:27,817 --> 00:11:32,584
-Girls, sit down.
-Aunt Iris, this is Phoebe and Rachel.

142
00:11:32,789 --> 00:11:36,691
Listen, I'm parked at a meter.
Let's do it. Okay?

143
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,028
We'll start with five-card draw.

144
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:46,169
Then we'll go into the studs and the
hold 'ems. I talked to Cousin Nathan.

145
00:11:46,369 --> 00:11:49,827
Don't touch the cards
when somebody is dealing.

146
00:11:54,544 --> 00:11:55,636
How is Nathan?

147
00:11:55,845 --> 00:11:59,406
Now he thinks he's a man
in a woman's body.

148
00:11:59,616 --> 00:12:02,710
Don't you mean
a woman in a man's body?

149
00:12:03,153 --> 00:12:05,383
It should be so simple.

150
00:12:15,965 --> 00:12:19,401
Ross, could we please listen
to anything else?

151
00:12:19,602 --> 00:12:21,502
All right.

152
00:12:37,487 --> 00:12:39,614
I'm gonna pay for that tonight.

153
00:12:45,095 --> 00:12:47,563
Hi. Guys, guess what?

154
00:12:47,764 --> 00:12:52,599
The fifth dentist caved, and now
they're all recommending Trident?

155
00:12:58,608 --> 00:13:00,667
No, the interview!

156
00:13:01,111 --> 00:13:03,978
Unbelievable!
She absolutely loved me.

157
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:08,082
We talked for over two hours.
We've the same taste in clothes.

158
00:13:08,284 --> 00:13:10,718
And I went to camp with her cousin.

159
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:15,380
-The job is perfect! I can do this.
-That's great!

160
00:13:15,592 --> 00:13:19,688
-Then she told a funny story.
-Great, tell us and we'll laugh.

161
00:13:19,896 --> 00:13:21,921
Let's play poker!

162
00:13:23,366 --> 00:13:27,860
Listen, we talked about it and
if you don't wanna play, it's okay.

163
00:13:28,071 --> 00:13:33,008
Yes, we can play some other game.
Like Pictionary?

164
00:13:34,811 --> 00:13:36,176
Very funny.

165
00:13:36,379 --> 00:13:40,406
-But we'd like to try poker again.
-Yes, I think we should.

166
00:13:40,617 --> 00:13:46,317
-Do you want me to shuffle those?
-That's okay, I'm gonna give it a go.

167
00:13:55,165 --> 00:13:58,157
So Pheebs owes $7.50.
Monica owes $10.00.

168
00:13:58,368 --> 00:14:01,360
And Rachel, you owe 15 big ones!

169
00:14:02,205 --> 00:14:07,541
Thanks for teaching us Cross-Eyed
Mary. We gotta play that other way.

170
00:14:08,378 --> 00:14:12,280
All right, here's my $7.50.
But this money is cursed.

171
00:14:12,482 --> 00:14:15,110
-What?
-I cursed it!

172
00:14:16,452 --> 00:14:19,319
Now bad things will happen
to the spender.

173
00:14:19,622 --> 00:14:23,490
I'll take it.
Bad things happen to me anyway.

174
00:14:24,027 --> 00:14:26,928
This way, I can split them up
with a movie.

175
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:32,432
So that just leaves the big Greene
poker machine, who owes 15.

176
00:14:33,937 --> 00:14:36,497
Could you be any smugger?

177
00:14:36,706 --> 00:14:40,301
Let's see. Rach, I'm opening up
a new art gallery...

178
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:45,538
...and I could sure use the portraits
of Lincoln and Hamilton.

179
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:51,214
It's so typical.
"I'm a man! I have a penis!

180
00:14:51,421 --> 00:14:55,619
I have to win money
to exert my power over women!"

181
00:14:58,695 --> 00:15:00,219
This isn't over.

182
00:15:00,563 --> 00:15:03,623
We'll play you again.
We'll win. You'll lose.

183
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,562
You'll beg. We'll laugh.

184
00:15:05,768 --> 00:15:11,001
We'll take every last dime you have.
And you'll hate yourselves forever!

185
00:15:13,176 --> 00:15:16,270
Kind of stepped on
my point there, Mon.

186
00:15:16,479 --> 00:15:19,880
I can't believe you lost!
How much did they take?

187
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:21,983
Like 30 bucks.

188
00:15:22,185 --> 00:15:24,881
-I'll give you that money back.
-Really?

189
00:15:25,088 --> 00:15:28,990
No, I'm bluffing!
You guys haven't learned crap!

190
00:15:31,728 --> 00:15:34,356
-Hand me the cards!
-Can I?

191
00:15:34,564 --> 00:15:36,361
Yes!

192
00:15:42,438 --> 00:15:48,434
Wanna give us your money now? We can
skip the formality of really playing.

193
00:15:48,645 --> 00:15:52,979
No, that's fine. We'll see who has
the last laugh, monkey boy.

194
00:15:55,885 --> 00:15:59,048
Done with chitchat?
Ready for serious poker?

195
00:15:59,255 --> 00:16:03,351
You guys, look! The one-eyed jack
follows me wherever I go.

196
00:16:04,627 --> 00:16:06,492
Right. Serious poker.

197
00:16:06,696 --> 00:16:11,395
-Mon, got any more of those salmon?
-You want to eat or play poker?

198
00:16:11,601 --> 00:16:14,764
-Where are you going?
-To the bathroom.

199
00:16:14,971 --> 00:16:17,769
Want to go to the bathroom
or play poker?

200
00:16:17,974 --> 00:16:19,601
Go to the bathroom.

201
00:16:21,978 --> 00:16:24,572
-Well, I'm gonna order a pizza.
-No!

202
00:16:24,781 --> 00:16:29,684
I'm waiting to hear from that job.
The store closes at 9:00. Eat then.

203
00:16:29,886 --> 00:16:34,084
That's fine. I'll just have a Tic Tac
to hold me over.

204
00:16:34,791 --> 00:16:39,125
All right. Cincinnati. No blinds.
Everybody, ante.

205
00:16:39,329 --> 00:16:40,318
Yes!

206
00:16:41,531 --> 00:16:43,465
Or no.

207
00:16:45,335 --> 00:16:50,432
-All right! Your money's mine, Greene.
-Your fly's open, Geller.

208
00:16:56,346 --> 00:17:02,342
You know what I just realized?
Joker is poker with a "J"!

209
00:17:04,687 --> 00:17:06,154
Coincidence?

210
00:17:07,423 --> 00:17:11,325
That's jo-incidence with a "C"!

211
00:17:21,904 --> 00:17:25,135
-Phoebe?
-Yeah, I'm out.

212
00:17:26,175 --> 00:17:28,803
-I'm in.
-Me too.

213
00:17:29,012 --> 00:17:30,877
Me too.
What do you got?

214
00:17:31,547 --> 00:17:36,280
You better hop out of the shower,
because I got a flush.

215
00:17:39,188 --> 00:17:40,815
Well, well, well!

216
00:17:41,090 --> 00:17:45,857
Hop back in, bucko,
because I got four sixes!

217
00:17:46,095 --> 00:17:50,122
I got four sixes! I won!
I actually won! Oh, my God!

218
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:53,427
You know what?
I'll make a little Ross pile.

219
00:17:53,636 --> 00:17:54,796
Look!

220
00:17:55,004 --> 00:17:59,907
I think that one was Ross'.
And I think that one was Ross'.

221
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:05,178
<i>Well, I have got your money
And you'll never see it</i>

222
00:18:05,381 --> 00:18:07,645
<i>And your fly's still open</i>

223
00:18:07,884 --> 00:18:09,852
<i>I made you look</i>

224
00:18:12,722 --> 00:18:15,316
-I'm in.
-I couldn't be in-er.

225
00:18:15,525 --> 00:18:18,119
Monica, in or out?

226
00:18:18,528 --> 00:18:20,621
I hate this game!

227
00:18:28,471 --> 00:18:29,904
Joey, your bet.

228
00:18:30,106 --> 00:18:33,337
I fold like a hooker
who got hit in the stomach...

229
00:18:33,609 --> 00:18:36,578
...by a fat guy
with sores on his face.

230
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:41,311
I'm out.

231
00:18:42,852 --> 00:18:46,015
-Ross?
-I'm very in.

232
00:18:46,656 --> 00:18:48,920
-Chandler?
-Couldn't be more out.

233
00:18:49,125 --> 00:18:51,923
Me too. Rachel?

234
00:18:52,328 --> 00:18:58,324
I will see you and I'll raise you.
Do you wanna waste another buck?

235
00:18:59,268 --> 00:19:02,032
No, not this time.
What did you have?

236
00:19:02,238 --> 00:19:04,138
-I'm not telling.
-Show them.

237
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:05,398
-No.
-Show them!

238
00:19:05,608 --> 00:19:09,704
-Get your hands out of there!
-I've had dates like this.

239
00:19:11,914 --> 00:19:14,974
Boy, you really can't stand
to lose, can you?

240
00:19:15,251 --> 00:19:20,518
Your whole face is getting red.
Veins popping out of your temple!

241
00:19:20,723 --> 00:19:24,090
Plus, that shirt doesn't really
match those pants.

242
00:19:27,897 --> 00:19:31,230
-I'm not losing.
-You're definitely losing.

243
00:19:31,434 --> 00:19:33,402
Hello. Rachel Greene.

244
00:19:35,271 --> 00:19:38,138
Excuse me. It's about the job!

245
00:19:38,741 --> 00:19:41,073
Barbara, hi! How are you?

246
00:19:45,882 --> 00:19:48,180
No, I understand.

247
00:19:49,685 --> 00:19:53,951
Come on. No, I'm fine.
Don't be silly. Yeah.

248
00:19:54,157 --> 00:19:57,923
But if anything else
opens up, please...

249
00:19:58,127 --> 00:19:59,754
Hello?

250
00:20:17,847 --> 00:20:19,041
Sorry, Rach.

251
00:20:19,549 --> 00:20:22,484
There's gonna be lots
of other stuff.

252
00:20:22,685 --> 00:20:24,209
Okay.

253
00:20:25,154 --> 00:20:27,054
Where were we?

254
00:20:27,890 --> 00:20:33,624
Five-card draw. Jacks are better.
Nothing wild. Everybody, ante.

255
00:20:34,497 --> 00:20:39,230
-Look, Rach, we don't have to do this.
-Yes, we do.

256
00:20:41,537 --> 00:20:43,630
-All right. Check.
-Check.

257
00:20:44,006 --> 00:20:47,134
-I'm in for 50 cents.
-Call.

258
00:20:47,343 --> 00:20:49,140
I'm in.

259
00:20:49,545 --> 00:20:52,139
I see your 50 cents...

260
00:20:52,348 --> 00:20:55,840
...and I raise you $5.

261
00:20:56,686 --> 00:20:59,018
I thought it was a 50-cent limit.

262
00:20:59,222 --> 00:21:02,157
I just lost a job,
I'd like to raise it $5.

263
00:21:02,358 --> 00:21:04,826
Does anyone have
a problem with that?

264
00:21:05,394 --> 00:21:07,589
-Not at all.
-No.

265
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:13,291
Loser?

266
00:21:21,177 --> 00:21:25,045
-No, I fold.
-What do you mean, you fold?

267
00:21:25,281 --> 00:21:29,684
I thought that, "Once the cards
are dealt, I'm not a nice guy."

268
00:21:29,919 --> 00:21:32,513
Were you just full of it?

269
00:21:45,635 --> 00:21:46,693
I'm in.

270
00:21:47,536 --> 00:21:49,697
-How many do you want?
-One.

271
00:21:51,207 --> 00:21:53,141
Dealer takes two.

272
00:21:53,509 --> 00:21:56,444
-What do you bet?
-I bet $2.

273
00:21:58,080 --> 00:22:00,981
Okay. I see your $2...

274
00:22:01,183 --> 00:22:03,913
...and I raise you...

275
00:22:05,187 --> 00:22:06,882
...20.

276
00:22:11,694 --> 00:22:13,559
I see your $20...

277
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:16,655
...raise you $25.

278
00:22:22,104 --> 00:22:26,234
I see your $25
and Monica, get my purse.

279
00:22:31,981 --> 00:22:34,575
Rachel, there's nothing in it.

280
00:22:35,651 --> 00:22:38,142
Okay, then get me your purse.

281
00:22:43,159 --> 00:22:46,060
-Here you go. Good luck!
-Thank you.

282
00:22:46,562 --> 00:22:50,123
I saw your $25 and I raise you...

283
00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:52,657
...seven.

284
00:22:53,235 --> 00:22:54,793
-teen!

285
00:23:02,845 --> 00:23:05,370
Joey, I'm a little shy.

286
00:23:05,748 --> 00:23:08,911
That's okay, Ross. You can ask me.

287
00:23:14,857 --> 00:23:16,825
-What do you need?
-15.

288
00:23:17,026 --> 00:23:18,960
-Here's 10.
-I got 5.

289
00:23:19,161 --> 00:23:21,254
-Thank you.
-Good luck.

290
00:23:22,264 --> 00:23:24,994
I am calling your 17.

291
00:23:25,201 --> 00:23:27,032
What do you got?

292
00:23:37,613 --> 00:23:39,706
Full house.

293
00:23:46,088 --> 00:23:47,715
You got me.

294
00:23:58,367 --> 00:24:01,165
-That's tough to beat.
-I thought we had it!

295
00:24:01,370 --> 00:24:05,272
When you don't have the cards,
you don't have the cards.

296
00:24:05,474 --> 00:24:07,908
But look how happy she is.

297
00:24:17,787 --> 00:24:20,688
-Airmail.
-Airplane. <i>Airport. Airport '75!</i>

298
00:24:20,890 --> 00:24:24,121
<i>Airport '77! Airport '79!</i>

299
00:24:24,727 --> 00:24:26,319
Time's up!

300
00:24:26,529 --> 00:24:29,157
<i>Bye Bye Birdie!</i>

301
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,093
That's a bird?

302
00:24:33,302 --> 00:24:35,634
That's a bird!

303
00:24:36,338 --> 00:24:38,806
Okay, it's my turn.

304
00:24:40,309 --> 00:24:41,742
Go!

305
00:24:43,946 --> 00:24:46,380
Bean! Bean!

306
00:24:47,817 --> 00:24:50,285
<i>The Unbearable Lightness of Being!</i>

307
00:24:53,556 --> 00:24:55,251
That you get?

308
00:24:55,458 --> 00:24:57,722
That you get?!
